The paper deals with memory-constrained algorithms and applies the compressed stack technique to solve various geometric problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), and Symbolic Computation (cs.SC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses time complexity and trade-offs, which could also place it in the Complexity Theory (cs.CC) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
